<center>Week One
----------------------------------------
####<center><i>The History of Design </center>
#####<center>Cave Paintings.</center>

Art and design has been around for a very long time and has evolved from very basic naturally created pieces to digial design and modern art.  The earliest cave painting to date was found in El Castillo in the Caves to Kells.  These crimson hands were created by Neanderthols approximatly 40,800 years ago and were discovered in 2012.
<br>
<br>
<center><i>El Castillo - Panel of Hands</i></center>
<center><img src="http://images.nationalgeographic.com/wpf/media-live/photos/000/549/cache/spain-cave-art-dated-oldest_54922_990x742.jpg" style="width:304px;height:280px"></center>
<br>
<br>
<center><i>El Castillo - Panel of Hands.</i></center>
<center><img src="http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2014/10/08/1412783908928_Image_galleryImage_article_2159197_139A477B0.JPG" style="width:304px;height:280px"></center>

There are many famous aboriginal cave painings.  Many of these cave drawings were of animals and other natural art as they would draw what they could see.  The artists used natural resources with matte, plain coloursand made use of dots to create texture and pattern.
<br>
<br>
<center><i>Cave Painting - Horses.</i></center>
<center><img src="http://www.donsmaps.com/images17/pechemerle.jpg" style="width:304px;height:260px"></center>
<br>
<br>
<center><i>Cave Painting - Buffalo.</i></center>
<center><img src="http://www.mazzaroth.com/ChapterOne/Images/LascauxCavePaint1.gif" style="width:304px;height:200px"></center>
<br>
<br>
<center><i>Cave Painting - Horse.</i></center>
<center><img src="http://therepublicofless.files.wordpress.com/2010/03/cave_painting_horse.jpg" style="width:304px;height:210px"></center>

The development from Cave paintings to modern art is phonomenal and it is interesting to see the skill in the work especially with their lack of resources.  Modern art however can be based on aboriginal art.  For example Prometheus has a famous Scottish cave painting within it's scenes in which the painting has been modernised with scientific equiptment within the film.  The original drawing was taken and placed on a large digital screen combined with the use of bright neon colours and shapes to create a futuristic effect.  This combination of ancient and modern art create a very nice effect.

<br>
<br>
<center><i>Cave Painting - Original.</i></center>
<center><img src="https://skinwalker.files.wordpress.com/2012/08/prometheus_cave_painting.jpeg?w=593" style="width:304px;height:210px"></center>
