Moving Image officially began in the 1800's however it argueable to an extent that cave paintings are a form of moving image as they represent the movement of natrual beings such as animals.
<br>
<br>
<center><i>Chauvet Caves</i></center>
<center><img src="http://www.theartnewspaper.com/imgart/Chauvet-caves.jpg"ropes style="width:304px;height:260px"></center>

Before the invention of moving imagine people used image and craft in order to create the illusion of moving image.  Examples of this are thaumatropes, zoetropes and phenakistoscopes.
<br>
<br>
<center><i>Thaumatrope</i></center>
<center><img src="http://www.bekkahwalker.net/comt111a/websites_12/lee_dami_site/Images/thaumatrope.jpg"ropes style="width:304px;height:260px"></center>
<br>
<br>
<center><i>Zoetrope</i></center>
<center><img src="https://www.mhs.ox.ac.uk/wp-content/uploads/zoetrope.png"ropes style="width:304px;height:330px"></center>
<br>
<br>
<center><i>Phenakistoscope</i></center>
<center><img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/8a/Phenakistoscope_3g07690u.jpg"ropes style="width:304px;height:300px"></center>

In 29 Sony created the world's largest Zoetrope at 33 feet.  This advertised ther Bravia TV and showed a footballer.  This interesting mix of old and new moving image was heavily praised and received a lot of good review.
<br>
<br>
<center><i>Sony Zoetrope</i></center>
<center><img src="http://www.creativereview.co.uk/images/uploads/2009/02/zoetrope_003.jpg"ropes style="width:304px;height:220px"></center>
In 1882 Eudweard Muybridge created 'The Horse in Motion' in order to answer the question 'Do horses ever lift all four hooves off the ground when running?'.  He took multiple photographs along a racetrack and put them in order to see if the myth was true which it turned out to be.  Later the photographs were put together to create a moving image almost like a GIF.
<br>
<br>
<center><i>The Horse in Motion</i></center>
<center><img src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/73/The_Horse_in_Motion.jpg"ropes style="width:304px;height:220px"></center>

the first motion picture was created by the Lumeer brothers and was called 'L'Arroseur arrosé' (The Waterer Watered) in 1895
<br>
<br>
<center>L'Arroseur arrosé</i></center>
<center><img src="http://rymimg.com/lk/f/l/4bce776577938574cc20ceb59c4a3458/1013521.jpg"ropes style="width:304px;height:220px"></center>

